  "text": "Srivastava (2016) showed analytically for anti-plane shear waves that k 2 and P 2 share the same sign, and hence so does P 2 . Therefore, the macroscopic transport of energy of anti-plane shear waves in the x 2 direction is aligned with the local transport. This implies that in the canonical configuration of excitation [CITATION_1] , i.e., when the laminate is impinged by a wave at a boundary normal to the lamination direction (Fig. 1b) , anti-plane shear will always refract positively. The reason is that continuity requires the excited Bloch waves to share the same vertical wavenumber as the incident wave, and hence the incident angle and the angle of the Bloch waves have the same sign. In the present problem, where P 2 is",
